<GlossaryTerm id="CDR0000044659"><TermName>dehydration</TermName><TermPronunciation>(dee-hy-DRAY-shun)</TermPronunciation><TermDefinition><DefinitionText>A condition caused by the loss of too much water from the body. Severe diarrhea or vomiting can cause dehydration.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></TermDefinition><MediaLink ref="CDR0000728054" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;dehydration&quot;" language="en" id="_3"/><MediaLink ref="CDR0000728053" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;deshidratación&quot;" language="es" id="_4"/><SpanishTermName>deshidratación</SpanishTermName><SpanishTermDefinition><DefinitionText>Afección causada por una pérdida excesiva de agua del cuerpo. La diarrea o los vómitos graves pueden causar deshidratación.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></SpanishTermDefinition></GlossaryTerm>
